
[1]captious

   CAPTIOUS, a.

   1. Disposed to find fault, or raise objections; apt to cavil, as in
   popular language, it is said, apt to catch at; as a captious man.

   2. Fitted to catch or ensnare; insidious; as a captious question.

   3. Proceeding from a caviling disposition; as a captious objection or
   criticism.
